Pick out the loser

head, tail, arrange, sort, order

loser <- tail(voteCount,1)

conditional choice

removeOne <- function(V,who=NULL,round=0){
  if(is.null(who)) {
    # Find the person with the lowest vote total
    group_by(V,currentVote) %.% dplyr::tally(sort=TRUE) %.% 
      filter(currentVote!='none') -> tmp
    who <- tail(tmp,1)$currentVote
  }
  message(paste('Candidate dropped:', who))
  return( 
    mutate(V,
           Third=ifelse(Third==who,'none',Third),
           Second=ifelse(Second==who,Third,Second),
           First=ifelse(First==who,Second,First),
           whichGroup=ifelse(currentVote==First,whichGroup,currentVote),
           currentVote=First
           )
    )
  }

Work through the process

makePlot <- function(Votes) {
  group_by(Votes,currentVote,whichGroup) %.% dplyr::tally(sort=TRUE) %.%
filter(currentVote != 'none') -> Counts
  ggplot(data=Counts,aes(x=reorder(currentVote,n),y=n ,fill=whichGroup))+geom_bar(stat='identity',position=position_stack(width=.9)) + theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=60,hjust=1)) + xlab("") + ylab('Number of Votes')
  }

The sequence of plots

step <- simpleVotes
